description:
Buzzkill is a four-part mini-series about drug abuse, religion, and super powers; created, written and illustrated by newcomers Donny Cates, Mark Reznicek, Geoff Shaw, and Lauren Affe.

If you've never been to an AA meeting before you should join Ruben and his group!

Collected in Buzzkill.
name: Buzzkill

description:
The story's protagonist, Barnabus, is a fallen angel in possession of a trinket that Satan is trying to recover. He is stuck between Heaven and Hell, doing the bidding of an angel named Jules while being chased by demons. His assignment received in issue #1 is to help a vampire seer named Verona escape from a werewolf (lycan) pack headed by Cassian Steele, who you figure out from the newspaper on page one is a mafia boss in New Orleans of some sort.

Collected in Kiss Me, Satan!.
name: Kiss Me, Satan!

description: In this comics-like children's book, big brother Benny and baby sister Penny are unhappy to hear that they have a playdate with their cousin, Bo. Why? Because Bo is a Toy Breaker. He's a pup (that's the term for mouse young, believe it or not) that parents and passersby might describe as "just too much"--too obnoxious, too pushy, and too rough with other pups' stuff. Bo must learn to play well with others (and their toys), while Benny and Penny must learn to give their cousin a second chance.
name: Benny and Penny in the Toy Breaker
